SIMPLE: miscarriage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miscarriage
<hw>Mis*car"riage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Unfortunate event or issue of an undertaking; failure to attain a
proper or desired result or reach a destination; <as>as, a serious
<ex>miscarriage</ex> of justice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When a counselor, to save himself,⟦br⟧
Would lay <qex>miscarriages</qex> upon his prince.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Ill conduct; evil or improper behavior; <as>as, the
failings and <ex>miscarriages</ex> of the righteous</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Rogers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act of bringing forth a child before the time it
is viable; a premature birth, resulting in death of the fetus;
spontaneous abortion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miscarriageable</ent>⟦br⟧
